Phone scammers impersonating ACSC | Cyber.gov.au
Description: Telephone scams - where people pretend to be from a reputable organisation to try to get access to your computer and your bank account - are a constant threat. The ACSC is aware of a new scam where people call who pretend to be from the ACSC, seeking your help to act against cyber criminals. These scammers try to coax individuals into actions that could compromise computers or reveal bank information. These types of scams are also called ‘remote access scams’ or impersonation scams.
